orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_bbc452d988cb10ebac29581b638f515f" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_db86ab4cfb6ec9ab5dfc2cfd57316537" parent="aspace_bbc452d988cb10ebac29581b638f515f" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_ca7acf877559d7db70e13bed442b6b8c" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_8b58b921556c7e73842e8ab32c8cca6d" parent="aspace_ca7acf877559d7db70e13bed442b6b8c" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_1771e64052b4acf6c354d5dfbd17bc38" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1e7f7d759175dcbcda0e44d9d5d63726" parent="aspace_1771e64052b4acf6c354d5dfbd17bc38" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-